h245ConfigurationTable.name: h245ConfigurationTable
h245ConfigurationTable.description: This table contains information about H.245 configuration parameters. It is a list of configuration parameter entries. The number of entries equals to the number of H.245 stacks in a system.

h245ConfigurationTableEntry.name: h245ConfigurationTableEntry
h245ConfigurationTableEntry.description: It contains objects that describe the H.245 configuration parameters.

h245ConfigT101Timer.name: h245ConfigT101Timer
h245ConfigT101Timer.description: This timer is used during Capability Exchange procedure. This timer is used in the AWAITING RESPONSE state. It specifies the maximum time during which no TerminalCapabilitySetAck or TerminalCapabilitySetReject message may be received.

h245ConfigT102Timer.name: h245ConfigT102Timer
h245ConfigT102Timer.description: This timer is used during Maintenance Loop procedure. This timer is used during the AWAITING RESPONSE state. It specifies the maximum allowed time during which no MaintenanceLoopAck or MaintenanceLoopReject message may be received .

h245ConfigT103Timer.name: h245ConfigT103Timer
h245ConfigT103Timer.description: This timer is used during Uni-directional and Bi-directional Logical Channel Signalling procedure. This timer is used in the AWAITING ESTABLISHMENT and AWAITING RELEASE states. It specifies the maximum time during which no OpenLogicalChannelAck or OpenLogicalChannelReject or CloseLogicalChannelAck message may be received.

h245ConfigT104Timer.name: h245ConfigT104Timer
h245ConfigT104Timer.description: This timer is used during H.223 Multiplex Table procedure. This timer is used in the AWAITING RESPONSE state. It specifies the maximum time during which no MultiplexEntrySendAck or MultiplexEntrySendReject message may be received.

h245ConfigT105Timer.name: h245ConfigT105Timer
h245ConfigT105Timer.description: This timer is used during Round Trip Delay procedure. This timer is used in the AWAITING RESPONSE state. It specifies the maximum time during which no RoundTripDelayResponse message may be received.

h245ConfigT106Timer.name: h245ConfigT106Timer
h245ConfigT106Timer.description: This timer is used during Master Slave Determination procedure. This timer is used in the OUTGOING AWAITING RESPONSE state and during the INCOMING AWAITING RESPONSE state. It specifies the maximum time during which no acknowledgement message may be received.

h245ConfigT107Timer.name: h245ConfigT107Timer
h245ConfigT107Timer.description: This timer is used during Request Multiplex Entry procedure. This timer is used during the AWAITING RESPONSE state. It specifies the maximum time during which no RequestMultiplexEntryAck or RequestMultiplexEntryReject message may be received.

h245ConfigT108Timer.name: h245ConfigT108Timer
h245ConfigT108Timer.description: This timer is used during SEND Logical Channel procedure. This timer is used in the AWAITING RESPONSE state. It specifies the maximum time during which no RequestMultiplexEntryAck or RequestMultiplexEntryReject message may be received.

h245ConfigT109Timer.name: h245ConfigT109Timer
h245ConfigT109Timer.description: This timer is used during Mode Request procedure. This timer is used in the AWAITING RESPONSE state. It specifies the maximum time during which no RequestModeAck or RequestModeReject message may be received.

h245ConfigN100Counter.name: h245ConfigN100Counter
h245ConfigN100Counter.description: This counter specifies the maximum number of times that MasterSlaveDetermination messages will be sent during the OUTGOING AWAITING RESPONSE state.

h245ControlChannelStatsTable.name: h245ControlChannelStatsTable
h245ControlChannelStatsTable.description: This table contains information about H.245 statistics. It is a list of statistics entries. The number of entries equals to the number of control channels for all H.245 stacks in a system.

h245ControlChannelStatsTableEntry.name: h245ControlChannelStatsTableEntry
h245ControlChannelStatsTableEntry.description: It contains objects that describe the H.245 control channel statistics.

h245ControlChannelNumberOfListenPorts.name: h245ControlChannelNumberOfListenPorts
h245ControlChannelNumberOfListenPorts.description: The number of H245 Listen ports. These ports are used for the remote entity to send a connect on

h245ControlChannelMaxConnections.name: h245ControlChannelMaxConnections
h245ControlChannelMaxConnections.description: The number of maximum active h245 channels allowed.

h245ControlChannelNumberOfListenFails.name: h245ControlChannelNumberOfListenFails
h245ControlChannelNumberOfListenFails.description: The number of Listen fails. The fail could be due to exhaustion of system resources

h245ControlChannelNumberOfActiveConnecti.name: h245ControlChannelNumberOfActiveConnections
h245ControlChannelNumberOfActiveConnecti.description: The number of the active H245 connections.

h245ControlChannelMasterSlaveMaxRetries.name: h245ControlChannelMasterSlaveMaxRetries
h245ControlChannelMasterSlaveMaxRetries.description: The number of maximum master slave retries. Reties are needed when the result of master slave process is indeterminate

h245ControlChannelConnectionAttemptsFail.name: h245ControlChannelConnectionAttemptsFail
h245ControlChannelConnectionAttemptsFail.description: The number of failures when trying to connect to a listen port.

h245ControlChanneMasterSlavelDeterminati.name: h245ControlChanneMasterSlavelDeterminations
h245ControlChanneMasterSlavelDeterminati.description: The number of MSD messages sent from a MSDSE to a peer MSDSE for master/slave determination purpose.

h245ControlChannelMasterSlaveAcks.name: h245ControlChannelMasterSlaveAcks
h245ControlChannelMasterSlaveAcks.description: The number of acks that are used to confirm whether the terminal is the master terminal or the slave terminal, as indicated by decision. When decision is of type master, the terminal receiving this message is the master terminal and when decision is of type slave, it is the slave terminal.

h245ControlChannelMasterSlaveRejects.name: h245ControlChannelMasterSlaveRejects
h245ControlChannelMasterSlaveRejects.description: The number of rejects of the MasterSlaveDetermination message.

h245ControlChannelMasterSlaveT106Rejects.name: h245ControlChannelMasterSlaveT106Rejects
h245ControlChannelMasterSlaveT106Rejects.description: The number of rejects of the MasterSlaveDetermination message. When the cause is of type identicalNumbers, the rejection was due to the random numbers being equivalent and the terminal types being the same.

h245ControlChannelMasterSlaveMSDRejects.name: h245ControlChannelMasterSlaveMSDRejects
h245ControlChannelMasterSlaveMSDRejects.description: The number of MSD rejects of the MasterSlaveDetermination message. Rejects can happen due to different reasons like identical random number after maximum tries, timeouts...

h245ControlChannelNumberOfMasterSlaveInc.name: h245ControlChannelNumberOfMasterSlaveInconsistentFieldRejects
h245ControlChannelNumberOfMasterSlaveInc.description: The number of rejects of the MasterSlaveDetermination message. The cause is due to conflict in the status that both entities arrive to.

h245ControlChannelMasterSlaveMaxCounterR.name: h245ControlChannelMasterSlaveMaxCounterRejects
h245ControlChannelMasterSlaveMaxCounterR.description: The number of rejects of the MasterSlaveDetermination message. There are many reasons why the rejection could happen.

h245ControlChannelMasterSlaveReleases.name: h245ControlChannelMasterSlaveReleases
h245ControlChannelMasterSlaveReleases.description: The number of rejects due to a time out.

h245ControlChannelNumberOfTunnels.name: h245ControlChannelNumberOfTunnels
h245ControlChannelNumberOfTunnels.description: The number of the active H245 tunnels.

h245ControlChannelMasterSlaveTable.name: h245ControlChannelMasterSlaveTable
h245ControlChannelMasterSlaveTable.description: This table contains information about entities that are connected to this entity. It is a list of connection entries. The number of entries equals to the number of active connections.

h245ControlChannelMasterSlaveTableEntry.name: h245ControlChannelMasterSlaveTableEntry
h245ControlChannelMasterSlaveTableEntry.description: It contains objects that describe the status of the master slave determination procedure.

h245ControlChannelSrcAddressTag.name: h245ControlChannelSrcAddressTag
h245ControlChannelSrcAddressTag.description: It describes the type of address (IP v4, IPv6...) of the source

h245ControlChannelDesTAddressTag.name: h245ControlChannelDesTAddressTag
h245ControlChannelDesTAddressTag.description: It describes the type of address (IP v4, IPv6...) of the source

h245ControlChannelIndex.name: h245ControlChannelIndex
h245ControlChannelIndex.description: It is an arbitrary number that is being incremented by 1 for every entry in this table

h245ControlChannelMSDState.name: h245ControlChannelMSDState
h245ControlChannelMSDState.description: It describes the state of the master slave determination procdure. It can be OUTGOING WAITING RESPONSE, INCOMING WAITING RESPONSE, IDLE

h245ControlChannelTerminalType.name: h245ControlChannelTerminalType
h245ControlChannelTerminalType.description: Terminal type represents the type of H.323 terminal: 50 - terminal without MC 60 - gateway without MC 70 - terminal with MC but without MP 80 - gateway with MC but without MP 120 - gatekeeper with MC but without MP 160 - MCU with MC but without MP 90 - gateway with MC and Data MP 130 - gatekeeper with MC and Data MP 170 - MCU with MC and Data MP 100 - gateway containing MC with Data and audio MP 140 - gatekeeper containing MC with Data and audio MP 180 - MCU containing MC with Data and audio MP 110 - gateway containing MC with Data, Audio and Video MP 150 - gatekeeper containing MC with Data, Audio and Video MP 190 - MCU containing MC with Data, Audio and Video MP 240 - entity with active MC .

h245ControlChannelNumberOfMSDRetries.name: h245ControlChannelNumberOfMSDRetries
h245ControlChannelNumberOfMSDRetries.description: The number of tries of master slave determination before a meaningful result is concluded.

h245ControlChannelIsTunneling.name: h245ControlChannelIsTunneling
h245ControlChannelIsTunneling.description: This variable indicates if tunneling is used for this channel.

h245CapExchangeStatsTable.name: h245CapExchangeStatsTable
h245CapExchangeStatsTable.description: This table contains information about H.245 statistics for capabilities exchange procedure. It is a list of cap exchange statistics entries. The number of entries equals to the number of H.245 stacks in a system.

h245CapExchangeStatsTableEntry.name: h245CapExchangeStatsTableEntry
h245CapExchangeStatsTableEntry.description: It contains objects that describe statistics for H.245 cap exchange procedure.

h245CapExchangeSets.name: h245CapExchangeSets
h245CapExchangeSets.description: The total number of TerminalCapabilitySets that were sent and received by the local CESE (Capability Exchange Signalling Entity). A TerminalCapabilitySet is used for the intention to signal a terminal's capabilities to ensure that the only multimedia signals to be transmitted are those that can be received and treated appropriately by the receive terminal.

h245CapExchangeAcks.name: h245CapExchangeAcks
h245CapExchangeAcks.description: The total number of TerminalCapabilitySetAcks that were sent and received by local CESE (Capability Exchange Signalling Entity). A TerminalCapabilitySetAck is used as a confirmation for a TerminalCapabilitySet that was successfully received and processed.

h245CapExchangeRejects.name: h245CapExchangeRejects
h245CapExchangeRejects.description: The total number of TerminalCapabilitySetRejects that were sent and received by the local CESE (Capability Exchange Signalling Entity). A TerminalCapabilitySetReject is used to indicate a failure due to a specific error for a TerminalCapabilitySet that was received, but, yet to be fully processed.

h245CapExchangeRejectUnspecified.name: h245CapExchangeRejectUnspecified
h245CapExchangeRejectUnspecified.description: The total number of TerminalCapabilitySetRejects that were sent and received by the local CESE (Capability Exchange Signalling Entity) with the cause value set to unspecified. This means that there was no cause for the rejection of a TerminalCapabilitySet specified.

h245CapExchangeRejectUndefinedTableEntry.name: h245CapExchangeRejectUndefinedTableEntryUsed
h245CapExchangeRejectUndefinedTableEntry.description: The total number of TerminalCapabilitySetRejects that were sent and received by the local CESE (Capability Exchange Signalling Entity) with the cause value set to undefinedTableEntryUsed. This means that the cause of the rejection of a TerminalCapabilitySet was due to a capability descriptor made reference to a capability table entry number in the capability table of the TerminalCapabilitySet was not defined.

h245CapExchangeRejectDescriptorCapacityE.name: h245CapExchangeRejectDescriptorCapacityExceeded
h245CapExchangeRejectDescriptorCapacityE.description: The total number of TerminalCapabilitySetRejects that were sent and received by the local CESE (Capability Exchange Signalling Entity) with the cause value set to descriptorCapacityExceeded. This means that the cause of the rejection of a TerminalCapabilitySet was due to a terminal incapable of storing all of the information from the capabilityDescriptors of the TerminalCapabilitySet.

h245CapExchangeRejectTableEntryCapacityE.name: h245CapExchangeRejectTableEntryCapacityExeeded
h245CapExchangeRejectTableEntryCapacityE.description: The total number of TerminalCapabilitySetRejects that were sent and received by the local CESE (Capability Exchange Signalling Entity) with the cause value set to tableEntryCapacityExceeded. This means that the cause of the rejection of a TerminalCapabilitySet was due to a terminal incapable of storing some (indicated in the highestEntryNumberProcessed) or all (indicated in the noneProcessed) of the information from the capability table of the TerminalCapabilitySet.

h245CapExchangeReleases.name: h245CapExchangeReleases
h245CapExchangeReleases.description: The total number of TerminalCapabilitySetReleases that were sent and received by the local CESE (Capability Exchange Signalling Entity). This means that a response for a TerminalCapabilitySet was not received/issued in time. A timer expiry had occurred for the local CESE.

h245CapExchangeCapabilityTable.name: h245CapExchangeCapabilityTable
h245CapExchangeCapabilityTable.description: Contains all the local incoming and outgoing CESEs (Capability Exchange Signalling Entity) that currently exists in this terminal.

h245CapExchangeCapabilityTableEntry.name: h245CapExchangeCapabilityTableEntry
h245CapExchangeCapabilityTableEntry.description: Each entry contains either the local incoming or outgoing CESE (Capability Exchange Signalling Entity) that is derived from a particular H.245 Control Channel, Logical Channel 0, or H.245 session.

h245CapExchangeDirection.name: h245CapExchangeDirection
h245CapExchangeDirection.description: Represents either the local incoming CESE or the local outgoing CESE (Capability Exchange Signalling Entity).

h245CapExchangeState.name: h245CapExchangeState
h245CapExchangeState.description: The current state of this CESE (Capability Exchange Signalling Entity).

h245CapExchangeProtocolId.name: h245CapExchangeProtocolId
h245CapExchangeProtocolId.description: The version of the H.245 protocol used. This specifies how H.245 messages are formatted and used.

h245CapExchangeRejectCause.name: h245CapExchangeRejectCause
h245CapExchangeRejectCause.description: The latest reject cause value extracted from the latest TerminalCapabilitySetReject.

h245CapExchangeMultiplexCapability.name: h245CapExchangeMultiplexCapability
h245CapExchangeMultiplexCapability.description: The latest multiplexCapability extracted from a TerminalCapabilitySet.

h245CapExchangeCapability.name: h245CapExchangeCapability
h245CapExchangeCapability.description: The latest capabilityTable extracted from the latest TerminalCapabilitySet.

h245CapExchangeCapabilityDescriptors.name: h245CapExchangeCapabilityDescriptors
h245CapExchangeCapabilityDescriptors.description: The latest capabilityDescriptors extracted from the latest TerminalCapabilitySet.

h245LogChannelsChannelTable.name: h245LogChannelsChannelTable
h245LogChannelsChannelTable.description: Contains all the local incoming and outgoing LCSEs (Uni or Bi-directional Logical Channel Signalling Entity) that currently exist in this terminal with their logical channels open or in the process of being opened or closed.

h245LogChannelsChannelTableEntry.name: h245LogChannelsChannelTableEntry
h245LogChannelsChannelTableEntry.description: Each entry contains either the local incoming or outgoing LCSE (Uni or Bi-directional Logical Channel Signalling Entity) that is derived from a particular H.245 Control Channel, Logical Channel 0, or H.245 session with its logical channels that are currently open or in the process of being opened or closed.

h245LogChannelsChannelNumber.name: h245LogChannelsChannelNumber
h245LogChannelsChannelNumber.description: The forwardLogicalChannelNumber used to distinguish this media channel by this LCSE (Uni or Bi-directional Logical Channel Signalling Entity).

h245LogChannelsChannelDirection.name: h245LogChannelsChannelDirection
h245LogChannelsChannelDirection.description: Represents the direction of this media channel used by this LCSE (Uni or Bi-directional Logical Channel Signalling Entity) .

h245LogChannelsIndex.name: h245LogChannelsIndex
h245LogChannelsIndex.description: A unique value representing this media channel.

h245LogChannelsChannelState.name: h245LogChannelsChannelState
h245LogChannelsChannelState.description: The current state of the media channel which also represents the state of this LCSE (Uni or Bi-directional Logical Channel Signalling Entity).

h245LogChannelsMediaTableType.name: h245LogChannelsMediaTableType
h245LogChannelsMediaTableType.description: The actual media or data type used for this logical channel.

h245LogChannelsH225Table.name: h245LogChannelsH225Table
h245LogChannelsH225Table.description: Contains the H2250LogicalChannelParameters that are used in all of the logical channels that are currently opened on this terminal.

h245LogChannelsH225TableEntry.name: h245LogChannelsH225TableEntry
h245LogChannelsH225TableEntry.description: Each entry contains the actual specifics and options used in the H2250LogicalChannelParameters within a particular open logical channel.

h245LogChannelsSessionId.name: h245LogChannelsSessionId
h245LogChannelsSessionId.description: A unique RTP or T.120 Session Identifier in a conference. It is used by the transmitter to refer to the session to which the logical channel applies.

h245LogChannelsAssociateSessionId.name: h245LogChannelsAssociateSessionId
h245LogChannelsAssociateSessionId.description: This is used to associate one session with another in a conference. A typical use will be to associate an audio session with a video session to indicate which sessions to process for lip synchronization.

h245LogChannelsMediaChannel.name: h245LogChannelsMediaChannel
h245LogChannelsMediaChannel.description: Indicates a transporTAddress to be used for the logical channel.

h245LogChannelsMediaGuaranteedDelivery.name: h245LogChannelsMediaGuaranteedDelivery
h245LogChannelsMediaGuaranteedDelivery.description: Indicates whether or not the underlying media transport should be selected to provide or not to provide guaranteed delivery of data.

h245LogChannelsMediaControlChannel.name: h245LogChannelsMediaControlChannel
h245LogChannelsMediaControlChannel.description: Indicates the media control channel in which the sender of the open logical channel will be listening for media control messages for this session. This field is present only when a media control channel is required.

h245LogChannelsMediaControlGuaranteedDel.name: h245LogChannelsMediaControlGuaranteedDelivery
h245LogChannelsMediaControlGuaranteedDel.description: Indicates whether or not the underlying media control transport should be selected to provide or not to provide guaranteed delivery of data. This field is present only when a media control channel is required.

h245LogChannelsSilenceSuppression.name: h245LogChannelsSilenceSuppression
h245LogChannelsSilenceSuppression.description: Indicates whether the transmitter stops sending packets during times of silence for bandwidth reasons. This can only be enabled for an audio channel only.

h245LogChannelsDestination.name: h245LogChannelsDestination
h245LogChannelsDestination.description: Indicates the terminal label (composed of a mcu number and a terminal number) of the destination if one has been assigned.

h245LogChannelsDynamicRTPPayloadType.name: h245LogChannelsDynamicRTPPayloadType
h245LogChannelsDynamicRTPPayloadType.description: Indicates a dynamic payload value which is used in H.323 for the H.225.0 alternative H.261 video packetization scheme. This field is present only when a dynamic RTP payload is in use.

h245LogChannelsH261aVideoPacketization.name: h245LogChannelsH261aVideoPacketization
h245LogChannelsH261aVideoPacketization.description: Indicates that the H.261 alternative RTP payload form is in use as described in H.225.0.

h245LogChannelsRTPPayloadDescriptor.name: h245LogChannelsRTPPayloadDescriptor
h245LogChannelsRTPPayloadDescriptor.description: If the rfc-number is chosen, it indicates the offical document of the IETF in which the payload format is defined (OID). Obsolete RFCs should not be referenced here. If the oid component is chosen, this identifies a payload format specified as part of a Recommendation defined by the ITU or an International Standard defined by the ISO and registered in the respective document under this Object Indentifier.

h245LogChannelsRTPPayloadType.name: h245LogChannelsRTPPayloadType
h245LogChannelsRTPPayloadType.description: Indicates which payload type value used. If the dynamic payload type is used, the values of this field and the logChannelsDynamicRTPPayloadType should match.

h245LogChannelsTransportCapability.name: h245LogChannelsTransportCapability
h245LogChannelsTransportCapability.description: Indicates optional transport capabilites such as quality of service and median channel type capabilites.

h245LogChannelsRedundancyEncoding.name: h245LogChannelsRedundancyEncoding
h245LogChannelsRedundancyEncoding.description: Indicates which redundancy encoding modes are supported (if any). The redundancyEncoding indicates that the redundant encoding method indicated in this parameter is to be used for this logical channel. The primary encoding is defined by the dataType of the forwardLogicalChannelParameters or the reverseLogicalChannelParameters, respectively. The type of redundancy encoding to be applied for this logical channel is identified by the redundancyEncodingMethod parameter, the secondary encoding is specified in the secondaryEncoding parameter. The DataType (audio, video, etc.) selected for both primary and secondary encoding shall match and shall be in accordance with the redundancyEncodingMethod selected.

h245LogChannelsSrcTerminalLabel.name: h245LogChannelsSrcTerminalLabel
h245LogChannelsSrcTerminalLabel.description: This is used to identify the terminal number of the sender of the OpenLogicalChannel message.

h245LogChannelOpenLogicalChannelTable.name: h245LogChannelOpenLogicalChannelTable
h245LogChannelOpenLogicalChannelTable.description: This table contains information about statistics for H.245 open logical channels.It is a list of statistics entries. The number of entries equals to the number of control channels for all H.245 stacks in a system.

h245LogChannelOpenLogicalChannelTableEnt.name: h245LogChannelOpenLogicalChannelTableEntry
h245LogChannelOpenLogicalChannelTableEnt.description: It contains objects that describe statistics for H.245 open logical channel procedure.

h245LogChanOpenLogChanTotalRequests.name: h245LogChanOpenLogChanTotalRequests
h245LogChanOpenLogChanTotalRequests.description: The total number of attempts to open a uni-directional logical channel between an outgoing LCSE and a peer incoming LCSE and a bi-directional logical channel between an outgoing B-LCSE and a peer incoming B-LCSE.

h245LogChanOpenLogChanAcks.name: h245LogChanOpenLogChanAcks
h245LogChanOpenLogChanAcks.description: The total number of confirmations to accept an open logical channel request. This would represent the final stage of establishing a uni-directional channel that can be used for transmission.

h245LogChanOpenLogChanConfirms.name: h245LogChanOpenLogChanConfirms
h245LogChanOpenLogChanConfirms.description: The total number of confirmations used for the purpose of bi-directional channel signaling that the reverse channel is open and can be used for transmission. This represents the final stage of establishing a bi-directional channel that can be used for transmission in both directions.

h245LogChanOpenLogChanRejects.name: h245LogChanOpenLogChanRejects
h245LogChanOpenLogChanRejects.description: The total number of rejections used as a response to a request to open a uni or a bi-directional logical channel from a LCSE or B-LCSE.

h245LogChanOpenLogChanRejectUnspecified.name: h245LogChanOpenLogChanRejectUnspecified
h245LogChanOpenLogChanRejectUnspecified.description: The total number of rejections used as a response to a request to open a uni or a bi-directional logical channel from a LCSE or B-LCSE when the reason for the rejection was unspecified.

h245LogChanOpenLogChanRejectUnsuitableRe.name: h245LogChanOpenLogChanRejectUnsuitableReverseParameters
h245LogChanOpenLogChanRejectUnsuitableRe.description: The total number of rejections used as a response to a request to open a bi-directional logical channel from a B-LCSE when the reason for the rejection was the reverseLogicalChannelParameters in the OpenLogicalChannel were inappropriate.

h245LogChanOpenLogChanRejectDataTypeNotS.name: h245LogChanOpenLogChanRejectDataTypeNotSupported
h245LogChanOpenLogChanRejectDataTypeNotS.description: The total number of rejections used as a response to a request to open a uni or a bi-directional logical channel from a LCSE or B-LCSE when the reason for the rejection was due to a terminal not capable of supporting the desired dataType.

h245LogChanOpenLogChanRejectDataTypeNotA.name: h245LogChanOpenLogChanRejectDataTypeNotAvailable
h245LogChanOpenLogChanRejectDataTypeNotA.description: The total number of rejections used as a response to a request to open a uni or a bi-directional logical channel from a LCSE or B-LCSE when the reason for the rejection was due to a terminal not capable of supporting the desired dataType simultaneously with the dataTypes of logical channels that are already open.

h245LogChanOpenLogChanRejectUnknownDataT.name: h245LogChanOpenLogChanRejectUnknownDataType
h245LogChanOpenLogChanRejectUnknownDataT.description: The total number of rejections used as a response to a request to open a uni or a bi-directional logical channel from a LCSE or B-LCSE when the reason for the rejection was due to a terminal not understanding the dataType indicated in the OpenLogicalChannel.

h245LogChanOpenLogChanRejectDataTypeALCo.name: h245LogChanOpenLogChanRejectDataTypeALCombinationNotSupported
h245LogChanOpenLogChanRejectDataTypeALCo.description: The total number of rejections used as a response to a request to open a uni or a bi-directional logical channel from a LCSE or B-LCSE when the reason for the rejection was due to a terminal not capable of supporting the dataType indicated in OpenLogicalChannel simultaneously with the Adaptation Layer type indicated in H223LogicalChannelParameters.

h245LogChanOpenLogChanRejectMulticastCha.name: h245LogChanOpenLogChanRejectMulticastChannelNotAllowed
h245LogChanOpenLogChanRejectMulticastCha.description: The total number of rejections used as a response to a request to open a uni or a bi-directional logical channel from a LCSE or B-LCSE when the reason for the rejection was due to a multicast Channel that could not be opened.

h245LogChanOpenLogChanRejectInsuffientBa.name: h245LogChanOpenLogChanRejectInsuffientBandwdith
h245LogChanOpenLogChanRejectInsuffientBa.description: The total number of rejections used as a response to a request to open a uni or a bi-directional logical channel from a LCSE or B-LCSE when the reason for the rejection was because permission to use the requested bandwidth for the logical channel was denied.

h245LogChanOpenLogChanRejectSeparateStac.name: h245LogChanOpenLogChanRejectSeparateStackEstablishmentFailed
h245LogChanOpenLogChanRejectSeparateStac.description: The total number of rejections used as a response to a request to open a uni or a bi-directional logical channel from a LCSE or B-LCSE when the reason for the rejection was due to a request to run the data portion of a call on a separate stack failed.

h245LogChanOpenLogChanRejectInvalidSessi.name: h245LogChanOpenLogChanRejectInvalidSessionID
h245LogChanOpenLogChanRejectInvalidSessi.description: The total number of rejections used as a response to a request to open a uni or a bi-directional logical channel from a LCSE or B-LCSE when the reason for the rejection was due to an attempt by a slave to set the SessionID when opening a logical channel to the master.

h245LogChanOpenLogChanRejectMasterSlaveC.name: h245LogChanOpenLogChanRejectMasterSlaveConflict
h245LogChanOpenLogChanRejectMasterSlaveC.description: The total number of rejections used as a response to a request to open a uni or a bi-directional logical channel from a LCSE or B-LCSE when the reason for the rejection was due to an attempt by a slave to open a logical channel in which the master has determined a conflict may occur.

h245LogChanOpenLogChanRejectWaitForCommu.name: h245LogChanOpenLogChanRejectWaitForCommunicationMode
h245LogChanOpenLogChanRejectWaitForCommu.description: The total number of rejections used as a response to a request to open a uni or a bi-directional logical channel from a LCSE or B-LCSE when the reason for the rejection was due to an attempt to open a logical channel before MC has transmitted the CommunicationModeCommand.

h245LogChanOpenLogChanRejectInvalidDepen.name: h245LogChanOpenLogChanRejectInvalidDependentChannel
h245LogChanOpenLogChanRejectInvalidDepen.description: The total number of rejections used as a response to a request to open a uni or a bi-directional logical channel from a LCSE or B-LCSE when the reason for the rejection was due to an attempt to open a logical channel with a dependent channel specified which is not present.

h245LogChansOpenLogChanRejectReplacement.name: h245LogChansOpenLogChanRejectReplacementForRejected
h245LogChansOpenLogChanRejectReplacement.description: The total number of rejections used as a response to a request to open a uni or a bi-directional logical channel from a LCSE or B-LCSE when the reason for the rejection was due to a logical channel of the type attempted cannot be opened using the replacementFor parameter.

h245LogChannelCloseLogicalChannelTable.name: h245LogChannelCloseLogicalChannelTable
h245LogChannelCloseLogicalChannelTable.description: This table contains information about H.245 statistics for close logical channel procedure. It is a list of statistics entries. The number of entries equals to the number of control channels for all H.245 stacks in a system.

h245LogChannelCloseLogicalChannelTableEn.name: h245LogChannelCloseLogicalChannelTableEntry
h245LogChannelCloseLogicalChannelTableEn.description: It contains objects that describe statistics for H.245 close logical channel procedure.

h245LogChanCloseLogChannels.name: h245LogChanCloseLogChannels
h245LogChanCloseLogChannels.description: The number of attempts made by the outgoing LCSE or B-LCSE to close a logical channel between two peer LCSEs or B-LCSEs. Note - In the case of a bi-directional logical channel, this closes both forward and reverse channels. It is not possible to close one and not the other.

h245LogChanCloseLogChanAcks.name: h245LogChanCloseLogChanAcks
h245LogChanCloseLogChanAcks.description: The number of attempts made to confirm the closing of a logical channel connection.

h245LogChanCloseLogChanRequests.name: h245LogChanCloseLogChanRequests
h245LogChanCloseLogChanRequests.description: The number of attempts made by the outgoing CLCSE to request the closing of a logical channel connection between two peer LCSEs.

h245LogChanCloseLogChanRequestsAcks.name: h245LogChanCloseLogChanRequestsAcks
h245LogChanCloseLogChanRequestsAcks.description: The number of attempts made by the incoming CLCSE to indicate that the logical channel connection will be closed.

h245LogChanCloseLogChanRequestRejects.name: h245LogChanCloseLogChanRequestRejects
h245LogChanCloseLogChanRequestRejects.description: The number of attempts made by the incoming CLCSE to indicate that the logical channel connection will not be closed. The only valid cause value for rejecting to close a channel is unspecified.

h245LogChanCloseLogChanRequestReleases.name: h245LogChanCloseLogChanRequestReleases
h245LogChanCloseLogChanRequestReleases.description: The number of attempts made by the outgoing CLCSE in the case of a time out.

h245MiscRoundTripDelayTable.name: h245MiscRoundTripDelayTable
h245MiscRoundTripDelayTable.description: This table contains information about round trip delay tests. It is a list round trip delay entries. The number of entries equals to the number of tests performed.

h245MiscRoundTripDelayTableEntry.description: It contains information about the round trip delay messages.

h245MiscRTDState.name: h245MiscRTDState
h245MiscRTDState.description: The state of the round trip delay. It can be either idle or waiting for response.

h245MiscT105TimerExpired.name: h245MiscT105TimerExpired

h245MiscLastRTDRequestSent.name: h245MiscLastRTDRequestSent

h245MiscLastRTDRequestRcvd.name: h245MiscLastRTDRequestRcvd
h245MiscLastRTDRequestRcvd.description: Information about the last round trip delay request received.

h245MiscLastRTDResponseSent.name: h245MiscLastRTDResponseSent
h245MiscLastRTDResponseSent.description: Information about the last round trip delay response sent.

h245MiscLastRTDResponseRcvd.name: h245MiscLastRTDResponseRcvd
h245MiscLastRTDResponseRcvd.description: Information about the last round trip delay response received.

h245MiscMaintenanceLoopTable.name: h245MiscMaintenanceLoopTable
h245MiscMaintenanceLoopTable.description: This table contains information about maintenance loop mode. It is a list of maintenance loop entries. The number of entries equals to the number of maintenance loop procedures.

h245MiscMaintenanceLoopTableEntry.description: It contains entries that describe the maintenance loop procedure.

h245MiscMaintenanceLoopDirection.name: h245MiscMaintenanceLoopDirection
h245MiscMaintenanceLoopDirection.description: The direction could be either incoming or outgoing.

h245MiscMLState.name: h245MiscMLState
h245MiscMLState.description: The state of the channel which can be: not looped, waiting to be looped or looped.

h245MiscNumberOfRequests.name: h245MiscNumberOfRequests
h245MiscNumberOfRequests.description: Number of loop requests on that channel.

h245MiscNumberOfAcks.name: h245MiscNumberOfAcks
h245MiscNumberOfAcks.description: Number of maintenance loop acks on the channel.

h245MiscLastMLRequestOrAckType.name: h245MiscLastMLRequestOrAckType
h245MiscLastMLRequestOrAckType.description: The type of the last request or response received. The type can be either media or logical channel loop.

h245MiscMLMediaOrLogicalChannelLoopRejec.name: h245MiscMLMediaOrLogicalChannelLoopRejectChannelNumber
h245MiscMLMediaOrLogicalChannelLoopRejec.description: If the loop rejecte is of type media loop or logical channel loop then this represents the channel number for the logical channel.

h245MiscNumberOfRejects.description: Number of loop requests that got rejected.

h245MiscLastRejectType.name: h245MiscLastRejectType
h245MiscLastRejectType.description: The type of the last reject for the loop request.

h245MiscErrorCode.name: h245MiscErrorCode

h245ConferenceTerminalTable.name: h245ConferenceTerminalTable
h245ConferenceTerminalTable.description: This table contains information about the terminal charachteristics that are related to a conference. It is a list entries. The number of entries equals to the number of conferences.

h245ConferenceTerminalTableEntry.name: h245ConferenceTerminalTableEntry
h245ConferenceTerminalTableEntry.description: It contains objects that describe a terminal as a conference participant.

h245ConferenceTerminalLabel.name: h245ConferenceTerminalLabel
h245ConferenceTerminalLabel.description: The terminal label of this terminal

h245ConferenceControlChannelIndex.name: h245ConferenceControlChannelIndex
h245ConferenceControlChannelIndex.description: The index of the control channel table that identifies the control channel for the conference.

h245ConferenceBroadcaster.name: h245ConferenceBroadcaster
h245ConferenceBroadcaster.description: The indicator of the terminal being a broadcaster.

h245ConferenceConferenceChair.name: h245ConferenceConferenceChair
h245ConferenceConferenceChair.description: The indicator of the terminal being a conference chair.

h245ConferenceMultipoint.name: h245ConferenceMultipoint
h245ConferenceMultipoint.description: The indicator of the conference being a multipoint.

h245ConferenceStatsTable.name: h245ConferenceStatsTable
h245ConferenceStatsTable.description: This table contains information about conference statistics. It is a list of conference statistics entries. The number of entries equals to the number of conferences on all system interfaces.

h245ConferenceStatsTableEntry.description: It contains objects that describe conference statistics.

h245ConferenceBroadcastMyLogicalChannel.description: The number of attempts made by a terminal to transmit MCV command to force an associated MCU to broadcast its video signal used to transmit the picture of a chairman or VIP, alternatively to hold a picture source during the transmission of graphics.

h245ConferenceCancelBroadcastMyLogicalCh.description: The number of attempts made by a terminal to cancel MCV command.

h245ConferenceDropConference.name: h245ConferenceDropConference

h245ConferenceZeroDelay.name: h245ConferenceZeroDelay
h245ConferenceZeroDelay.description: The same meaning as the command ACZ defined in H.230.

h245ConferenceVideoFreezePicture.name: h245ConferenceVideoFreezePicture

h245ConferenceVideoFastUpdatePicture.name: h245ConferenceVideoFastUpdatePicture
h245ConferenceVideoFastUpdatePicture.description: The number of commands sent/received to enter the fast update mode.

h245ConferenceVideoSendSyncEveryGOB.description: The number of commands sent/received by video encoder to use sync for every GOB until the cancel command is received.
